FBIS4-32961 "drlat105_b_94003" FBIS-LAT-94-105 Daily Report 31 May 1994 Dominican Republic Haiti Aristide Said To Side With France on Invasion Aristide Said To Side With France on Invasion FL3105201494 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1030 GMT 31 May 94 FL3105201494 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio French BFN [Text] Jean-Claude Martineau has said Aristide will side with France and other countries so that he is not blamed for an invasion of Haiti. This weekend on a Montreal radio station, president-in-exile's spokesman detailed the avalanche strategy [strategie lavalassienne], in light of new developments in the Haitian crisis. He almost lost his temper in light of the pertinence of the questions of Compere Raymond Laurent, who had him unveil his government's priorities. Martineau clearly confessed that President Aristide will side with France and other countries so that he is not blamed for an invasion of Haiti.
